# 7. Learner Skill Profile Strategy

## 7.1 MVP Learner Skill Calculation

When a learner completes a lesson/course:

```txt
Completed lesson
  ↓
Find course_skills linked to lesson/module/track
  ↓
Increase learner_skills.proficiency_score
  ↓
Use this profile for job matching
```

Example scoring:

| Completion Evidence | Score |
|---|---:|
| Enrolled but not completed | 20 |
| Lesson completed | 50 |
| Module completed | 65 |
| Track completed | 80 |
| Quiz score > 80% | +10 |
| Project passed | +10 |

For your phrase “not partially, rather almost fully aligned”, define job eligibility threshold like this:

```txt
Strong Match:     >= 80%
Good Match:       65–79%
Learning Gap:     40–64%
Not Ready:        < 40%
```

In the learner-facing UI, show mostly Strong/Good matches. Do not flood them with low-relevance jobs.

---

## 7.2 Required vs Preferred Skill Logic

A job match should heavily penalize missing required skills.

Formula:

```txt
required_score = matched_required_weight / total_required_weight
preferred_score = matched_preferred_weight / total_preferred_weight
final_match = required_score * 0.75 + preferred_score * 0.25
```

Then apply blockers:

```txt
If required_score < 0.70:
  do not show as “Apply-ready”
```

This satisfies your “almost fully aligned” requirement.

