# 2. Strategic Scope

There should be three layers, shipped incrementally.

## Layer 1 — Job Market Signals

This is the `plan2.md` version.

Purpose:

- scrape public job posts,
- extract skill mentions,
- aggregate trending skills,
- show market insight dashboard.

Example insight:

> “React appeared in 41 frontend job posts this week, up 18% from last week.”

## Layer 2 — Job Role Intelligence

Instead of only aggregating by skill, group postings into normalized job roles.

Examples:

- Frontend Developer
- Junior Python Developer
- Data Analyst
- Digital Marketing Executive
- Office Assistant
- AI Prompting Specialist
- WordPress Developer
- Customer Support Executive
- Excel/Data Entry Operator

For each role, Fixeth should know:

- required skills,
- preferred skills,
- tools,
- average salary,
- experience level,
- source count,
- demand trend,
- which Fixeth courses teach the needed skills.

## Layer 3 — Personalized Learner-to-Job Matching

After course/track completion, each learner sees:

- jobs they are ready for,
- match percentage,
- matched skills,
- missing skills,
- related Fixeth lessons to close the gap,
- confidence level,
- apply link if source posting still exists.

Example:

> “You completed Git + Data Science Basics. You are a 78% match for Junior Data Analyst roles. You already match Excel, Python basics, Git, SQL basics. Missing: Power BI and dashboard reporting. Complete these 2 lessons to reach 90%+.”

